text: Marian I Needham (born 1941), is a female former athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== She represented England in the long jump at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:English female long jumpers Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Living people
title: Marian Needham
